(1)
East 134th Street (right, autos thereon), north side, east from Brown Place, showing the cleared area between East 134th and East 135th Streets which is being rebuilt into an approach to the Tri-borough Bridge. The buildings on the left face on the north side of East 135th Street.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from a point slightly westward.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, as seen from St. Anns Ave. The construction of the bridge approach necessitated the demolition of several hundred tenement buildings.

P. L. Sperr.
